quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  23,1,"Successful indeed are the believers."
  23,2,"Those who offer their Salât (prayers) with all solemnity and full submissiveness."
  23,3,"And those who turn away from Al-Laghw (dirty, false, evil vain talk, falsehood, and all that Allâh has forbidden)."
  23,4,"And those who pay the Zakât."
  23,5,"And those who guard their chastity (i.e. private parts, from illegal sexual acts)"
  23,6,"Except from their wives or (the slaves) that their right hands possess, - for then, they are free from blame;"
  23,7,"But whoever seeks beyond that, then those are the transgressors;"
  23,8,"Those who are faithfully true to their Amanât (all the duties which Allâh has ordained, honesty, moral responsibility and trusts) and to their covenants;"
  23,9,"And those who strictly guard their (five compulsory congregational) Salawât (prayers) (at their fixed stated hours)."
  23,10,"These are indeed the inheritors"